results.title: The Dimensions are shifting...but Doc's stuck in the Office!
Losing My Religion
results.description: Doc has his meeting with the Tempo 'investors' and shows them the Technomagik Virtual Reality helmets.  He is inadvertently sucked into the Magic Dimension and has to fight the Aspect of Catastrophe.

results.title: and Doctor Strange and Doctor Strange and Doctor Strange
Journey to the East [The Homecoming, Part One]
results.description: Doc and Wong have yet another fight (you would think they were married!), so Doc heads to Tibet to 'find himself'.  There he discovers that Baron Mordo has interfered with his life ever since he was a child.

results.title: The Disciple's Tale [The Homecoming, Part Two]
results.description: Baron Mordo reveals that he is dying of cancer and wants to make amends for planting a psychic construct in 8 year old Stephen Strange's mind that plagued him with invisible demons for many years.

results.title: Walking Into Yesterday [The Homecoming, Part Three]
results.description: Doc returns to his Nebraska boyhood home and discovers a single mom he once knew.  After spending several blissful days with Amanda and Jessica, he discovers he has cancer, and that it is Baron Mordo's fault.

results.title: Resurrection [The Homecoming, Part Four]
results.description: Doc discovers that Astrid Mordo, Baron Mordo's daughter, is to blame for transferring the cancer.  Baron Mordo reverses the process and has to kill his own daughter just before he succumbs to the cancer.

results.title: Fall of the Tempo, Part One of Two
After Life, Part One
results.description: Doc returns home (by plane) with Amanda and Jessica and then says goodbye.  In New York he closes down the Tempo and finally destroys the demon Xaos, but takes Wong to see Imei's true spirit in the 'Afterlife'.

results.title: Fall of the Tempo, Part Two of Two
Afterlife, Part Two
results.description: Doc brings back Afterlife from Purgatory, who goes on a rampage stealing souls.  After a brief struggle, Doc discovers that Afterlife is not really a demon, but a trapped Angel who is freed by Doc's love.
